SEARCH
Package se.swedenconnect.spring.saml.idp.authentication.provider.external

Interface UserRedirectAuthenticationProvider

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.security.authentication.AuthenticationProvider, UserAuthenticationProvider
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractUserRedirectAuthenticationProvider
public interface UserRedirectAuthenticationProvider extends UserAuthenticationProvider
If the user authentication is performed outside the SAML IdP Spring Security flow an UserRedirectAuthenticationProvider should be provided. The UserAuthenticationProvider.authenticateUser(Saml2UserAuthenticationInputToken) method of this provider should return a RedirectForAuthenticationToken that tells the Saml2UserAuthenticationProcessingFilter where to redirect the user agent for authentication.

The getResumeAuthnPath() tells the path on where we expect the result (ResumedAuthenticationToken) to be delivered and this will lead to that the resumeAuthentication(ResumedAuthenticationToken) is invoked.

Author:
Martin Lindström

    • getTokenRepository

      ExternalAuthenticatorTokenRepository getTokenRepository()
      The provider, or any of its subcomponents, uses an ExternalAuthenticatorTokenRepository to get hold of the RedirectForAuthenticationToken that is the input for the external authentication process. It also uses the repository to commit, or save, the result of an external authentication process (an Authentication object) before the user agent is redirected back to the Spring Security flow. These method returns the ExternalAuthenticatorTokenRepository that is used.
      Returns:
      an ExternalAuthenticatorTokenRepository
